name: Washburn County Recycling Drop-off Site - Spooner
Northwest CleanSweep HHW Program Information
materials: Glue & Adhesives; Aerosol Spray Cans; Antifreeze; Asbestos; Brake Fluid; Compact Fluorescent Lights; Computer (Recycling); Degreasers; Fertilizer; Fluorescent Lamps/Tubes; Freon Removal; Fungicides; Gasoline and Unwanted Fuels; Herbicides; Household Cleaners; Insecticides; Mercury Containing Items; Ni-Cd Batteries; Other Batteries; Unused Paint; Paint Donation; Paint Thinner; Pesticides; Photography Chemicals; Pool Chemicals; Batteries (Rechargeable); Solvents; Transmission Fluid; Oil Filters
notes: Do not mix chemicals together.  This program services the following counties: Ashland, Bayfield, Burnett, Douglas, Iron, Price, Rusk, Sawyer, Taylor, and Washburn.  Usually there are three collection events in each county during the Summer.  Collection events will also usually accept acetone, artist's paints and media, auto body repair products, battery acid, all types of cleaners, contact cement, driveway sealer, fiberglass epoxy, floor care products, solvent based glue, HID bulbs, laboratory chemicals, oven cleaner, paint stripper and thinner, parts cleaner, shellac, stain, varnish, turpentine, wood filler, and wood preservative.  Pre-registration may be required for businesses and farmers and some fees may apply.  Please call for program details.  This program will accept up to seventy pounds of HHW from households free of charge.  This program will not accept alkaline batteries, ammunition, appliances, biological waste, compressed gas cylinders, explosives, freon 11 and 12, latex paint, motor oil, radioactive materials, recyclables, or vehicle batteries.
